Residents of Girei town, have barricaded the Yola-Mubi highway Tuesday morning, protesting the release of kidnap suspects by police authority in Adamawa state. The leader of the protesters, Alhaji Saidu Hamman alleged that, 10 persons were killed, over N67 million was collected from the community as ransom paid to kidnappers. Hamman, lamented that, they were involved in assisting the police in the apprehension kidnappers, but at the end the suspects are release by the police. Motorists were stranded at Tasham Maiturare venue of the protest for hours, some of the placards reads, “AIG intervene, no to release of Kidnap suspects, “We arrest kidnappers police release them with impunity”. The youths leader further said the peaceful protest followed an emergency stakeholders meeting to fashion out ways of addressing insecurity in the area. “11 suspected kidnappers were arrested and handed over to the police, they were released with investigation was ongoing. “The peaceful protest is to channel our plight to Gov. Ahmadu Fintiri, and security services to come to our aid. “We risk our lives while efforts is been thwarted with this recent development. Reacting on the matter, DSP Suleiman Yahaya, the police PPRO said Assistant Commissioner of Police, has been deployed to the scene to address the matter. Yahaya said eight suspected kidnappers, was arrested charged to court for their various offenses. He said four other suspects have been transferred to the Force Intelligence Bureau (FIB), for further investigation while four others arraigned before magistrate court in the state “Public should not act upon insinuation but verify fact before organizing protest. “Blocking major roads and denying people smooth transit is an offense. The police image maker urged public to give useful information that, could led to the arrested to kidnappers and criminally minded individuals in the state.